<p class="p">In this study, a two-stage procedure was used to estimate households’ resilience index. During the first stage, eight resilience blocks were estimated using principal component analysis based on 30 indicators. These resilience blocks include climate change and variability (CCV), income and food access (IFA), access to water and health facilities (AWH), assets (A), adaptive capacity (AC), social capital (SC), access to basic services (ABS) and stability (S). Based on the factor loading of each indicator, the resilience index of each individual household was computed using the PCA following the equation as: 
